Tszyu Wins WBC Super Lightweight Title
WASHINGTON , November 29 ( Xinhua ) -- Russian-born Australian Kostya Tszyu won the vacant World Boxing Council super lightweight title in California , the United States , according to a report here today .
The referee stopped the bout at 2 minutes , 35 seconds of the fifth round when Cuban Diobelys Hurtado was badly beaten .
In another fight , Luisito Espinosa of the Philippines retained his World Boxing Council featherweight title when the referee stopped the bout with American Kennedy McKinney 47 seconds into the second round .
